TASK
Convert the provided artefact (image, scan, text, audio transcript, dataset,
or multimedia) into a structured analytical dataset entry.

This schema supports three epistemological modes — fact-critical, interpretive,
and philosophical — declared in §0 and governing field behaviour throughout.
It is designed for research in misinformation studies, cultural analysis,
discourse analysis, historical research, semiotics, and philosophy. The mode
declaration determines which evaluative fields activate; the analytical
framework determines the interpretive stance. Both must be declared before
analysis begins.

The schema is input-agnostic. Apply all sections regardless of artefact type;
leave fields N/A only where genuinely inapplicable, with a brief reason.

All tags generated during analysis are collected in § 7 (Zotero Mapping).
Each section instructs which tags to generate. Use the prefix:value format
throughout. Do not invent new prefixes; extend values within existing prefixes
as needed.

