## 0. METHODOLOGICAL DECLARATION

Before extraction begins, declare:

- analytical_framework:
    State the interpretive stance being applied.
    Do NOT default to "neutral" — all frameworks are positioned.
    → TAG: framework:[value]
      e.g. framework:discourse-analysis | framework:source-criticism |
           framework:rhetorical-analysis | framework:fact-checking |
           framework:content-analysis | framework:critical-discourse-analysis |
           framework:semiotics | framework:narrative-analysis |
           framework:archival-criticism

- analytical_mode:
    Declare the primary epistemological register of this analysis.
    This selection activates and suppresses specific fields downstream —
    follow the instructions in each affected section.

    [fact-critical | interpretive | philosophical | mixed]

    fact-critical  — primary question: is this accurate?
                     Activates: misinformation_risk and corroboration_status
                     full protocol.
                     Applies to: news articles, institutional reports,
                     political speech, social media posts, data claims.

    interpretive   — primary question: what does this mean and do?
                     Suppresses: misinformation_risk → replace with
                     epistemic_effect field in §5.
                     Reframes: corroboration_status → interpretive_grounding
                     in §5.
                     Applies to: cultural artefacts, historical documents,
                     media texts, propaganda, visual material, oral testimony.

    philosophical  — primary question: is this coherent and what does
                     it presuppose?
                     Suppresses: misinformation_risk and source_reliability
                     as informant-trust assessment.
                     Activates: conceptual claim types in §3,
                     intertextuality in §2, assumption stress-test as
                     primary analytical operation.
                     Applies to: theoretical texts, philosophical arguments,
                     normative documents, conceptual frameworks.

    mixed          — two or more modes apply to distinct parts of the
                     artefact. Specify which sections operate in which
                     mode and why.

    → TAG: mode:fact-critical | mode:interpretive | mode:philosophical |
           mode:mixed

- analyst_type: [human | AI | human+AI]
    → TAG: analyst:[value]

- analyst_id: [name, model version, or institutional affiliation]

- analysis_date: [ISO format]

- known_analyst_limitations:
    Declare limitations of the analyst as an epistemic agent, independent
    of this specific artefact. These are standing constraints that would
    apply to any analysis this analyst performs — competencies, positionality,
    domain knowledge gaps, access restrictions, linguistic range.
    Do NOT describe consequences for this specific analysis here — those
    belong in §5 limitations_of_this_analysis.
    For each limitation:
      - limitation_id: [L1, L2, …]
      - type: [language | domain-knowledge | access | temporal-distance |
               cultural-context | positionality | other — specify]
      - description: [one sentence — the standing constraint]
    → TAG (one per limitation): analyst-limit:[type value]
      e.g. analyst-limit:language | analyst-limit:domain-knowledge |
           analyst-limit:access | analyst-limit:temporal-distance |
           analyst-limit:cultural-context | analyst-limit:positionality

